<item>
            <title>[TIKA-2838] RTF document processing glues comment fields together with text without whitespace</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-2838</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See ManifoldCF ticket &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CONNECTORS-1591&quot; title=&quot;RTF comment parsing problem&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CONNECTORS-1591&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CONNECTORS-1591&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for a sample document and a description of the problem.  Basically, comment fields for RTF documents are glued together with no whitespace between them, while other document formats properly put in a space (e.g. .docx etc).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
